-- China Studies Private Bond Sales by Companies, Securities Times Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-08T23:38:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/china-studies-private-bond-sales-by-companies-securities-times-reports.html

          
          
             China is studying the introduction of
rules that would allow non-finance companies to sell bonds
privately to investors, the Securities Times reported today,
citing an unidentified official with the National Association of
Financial Market Institutional Investors.  
 The nation currently only allows public sales of company
bonds, the Shenzhen-based newspaper reported.  
